<div class="gc-necklace-hub page-width">
  <h1 class="gc-necklace-hub-heading">Indian Necklace Types for Dance, Temple Jewellery & Deity Alankaram</h1>
  <p class="gc-necklace-hub-intro">
    Learn the necklace names customers use when shopping for Bharatanatyam jewellery, Kuchipudi jewellery,
    real kemp jewellery, temple necklaces, and deity alankaram harams.
  </p>

  {% assign glossary_content = "
  <h2>Bharatanatyam Short Necklace / Addigai</h2>
  <p>A close-fitting dance necklace worn with the full Bharatanatyam or Kuchipudi set. It is often paired with a long haram for stage balance.</p>

  <h2>Long Haram</h2>
  <p>A longer necklace layer used in Bharatanatyam, Kuchipudi, bridal temple jewellery, and deity alankaram. For deities, size should be matched to idol height and chest width.</p>

  <h2>Kemp / Kempu Necklace</h2>
  <p>A traditional South Indian temple jewellery style using red, green, or white Kemp stones with antique gold-plated settings. It is popular for Bharatanatyam, Kuchipudi, arangetram, and bridal styling.</p>

  <h2>Deity Short Haram</h2>
  <p>A short necklace used for god and goddess idol alankaram. Fit depends on idol height, neck width, pendant size, and how the ornament sits on the idol.</p>

  <h2>Deity Long Haram</h2>
  <p>A longer deity necklace used for Lakshmi, Varalakshmi, Amman, Balaji, Krishna, and many other deity idols. Some designs are common across deities, while others suit specific deity forms.</p>
  " %}

  {% render 'auto-link-glossary', content: glossary_content %}

  <div class="gc-necklace-faq">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>What necklace is included in a Bharatanatyam set?</strong>
      <p>A regular set usually includes a long haram and short necklace, along with other set components like waist belt, headset, mattal, earrings, rakodi, nose ring, bajuband, and bangles.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>What is the difference between regular and Kemp jewellery?</strong>
      <p>Regular Bharatanatyam jewellery is a quality-focused dance range. Kemp or Kempu jewellery is a premium temple jewellery style using red, green, or white Kemp stones and traditional South Indian motifs.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <strong>How do I choose deity necklace size?</strong>
      <p>Match the necklace dimensions to idol height, chest width, and ornament position. Measuring-tape product images should be checked before ordering.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

